--  Prompt Breakdown:
--    \ESC[48;5;4;38;5;8m
--      sets bg to color 4 
--      sets fg to color 0    
--    \ESC[m
--      resets colors (bg/fg)
--      so bg will be transparent
--    \ESC[38;5;4m
--      sets fg to color 4 (to draw arrow)
--    \ESC[m
--      resets colors again, so haskell code will be normal color
--
-- (also, you can insert %s before/after λ to get "Prelude" and such)

